ions; whereas a higher coverage was required to separate Artemia from Chl-a-or SPM-dominated water. The mean absolute percentage difference of BSI values calculated from Rayleigh-corrected and top-of-atmosphere (TOA) reflectance was <4\% compared with surface reflectance derived BSI, and the relative difference in coverage area was < +/- 10\%. Lastly, time series analyses of Lake Aibi in northwest China and the Great Salt Lake in North America revealed that the annual areal coverage estimation of Artemia slicks based on BSI was a positive indicator of Artemia harvesting, which can facilitate the Artemia resource management.
