litical context, on the one hand, and the changes in higher education system, on the other hand, the academic profession has to define a new identity for itself. The “professionalisation” of academic profession is becoming more important as universities try to respond to issues relating to standards and quality, growing international competition, and generally “doing more with less”. © Springer Science+Business Media Dordrecht 2013.
