AB  - This research study is based on integrated applications of geographic information systems (GIS) and remote sensing. These applications have proved to have immense potential for upgrading the living standard of human society as a whole. One of the examples is the provision of unique solutions for achieving global communication even into remote areas. Moreover, storm-tracking radar and meteorological satellites are regularly utilized for more accurate weather forecasting and cyclone prediction. On the other hand, remote sensing satellites are providing value-added information for the management of disasters such as storms and floods. As GIS and remote sensing are important tools for natural resource management and environment monitoring, they have become an integral part in planning sustainable development worldwide. Myanmar is still well endowed with natural resources, such as forests, fertile lands, abundant fresh water and rich minerals. For systematic and fruitful exploitation and utilization of these natural resources on a sustainable basis, applications of GIS and remote sensing are essential in different fields of natural resource management and environment monitoring in Myanmar. In this context, GIS and remote sensing are important decision-supporting tools.
